## M5/M6 — private join link (added after the original PR push)

User added a third item: admin-toggleable "private join link" at `/id/<slug>/join`. The route renders the standard league page with the recruiting banner forced on regardless of `League.visibility`. Re-targeted from v1.93.0 (which collided with the in-flight Guest rework that landed first as PR #261) to **v1.94.0**.

### Implementation

- Schema: `League.privateJoinLinkEnabled Boolean @default(false)` (additive). Migration `20260601000001_league_private_join_link_enabled` generated via `prisma migrate diff` (offline; the canonical `prisma migrate dev --create-only` per the user's brief requires a DATABASE_URL the worktree doesn't have — diff-script fallback is documented in `docs/migration-sql-lessons.md`).
- `updateLeagueDetails` accepts `privateJoinLinkEnabled?: boolean`; validates type; persists.
- `<LeagueDetailsEditor>` renders a new "Enable Private Join Link" toggle. When on, shows the resulting URL (`t9l.me/id/<subdomain>/join`) with a copy-to-clipboard button. Includes a friendly no-subdomain fallback message when the league hasn't set a subdomain yet.
- New `Dashboard` props: `forceRecruitingBanner?: boolean` (additive override on the `recruiting && ...` mount gate, now `(recruiting || forceRecruitingBanner) && ...`) and `showPrivateJoinIndicator?: boolean` (renders the subtle "Private join link" pill above the banner).
- New route at `src/app/id/[slug]/join/page.tsx`. Same shape as `/id/<slug>/page.tsx` (mirrors data fetching + Dashboard render) but: (1) re-fetches the league row up front to gate on `privateJoinLinkEnabled === false → notFound()`, (2) passes `forceRecruitingBanner={true}` and `showPrivateJoinIndicator={true}`.
- `<RecruitingBanner>` grows a `forceRecruitingBanner?: boolean` marker prop. Not branched on today; reserved so future per-state copy tweaks ("you've been invited to apply") don't require a Dashboard signature change.

### Security note (surfaced for operator)

The URL is slug-based per the user's literal spec. **Anyone who guesses the slug + tries `/join` with the toggle on gets the recruitment page.** For PRIVATE leagues this is a real (if low-severity) exposure.

Alternative not built this PR (operator can request as follow-up):
- Add `League.privateJoinToken: String?` (cuid).
- Require `/id/<slug>/join/<token>` instead of `/id/<slug>/join`.
- Toggle on regenerates the token; toggle off clears it.
- Stronger but admin must copy the full URL with token — slight UX cost.

`applyToLeague` server action unchanged: PRIVATE leagues still return "invitation-only" via the modal on submit. The banner being visible is necessary but not sufficient for submission on PRIVATE. For self-serve apply via the private-join URL to fully work, pair the toggle with PUBLIC_CLOSED visibility.

### Tests

- New `tests/unit/v194_private_join_link.test.ts` (19 tests).
- Renamed `tests/unit/v193_onboarding_skip_id_and_preferred_cap.test.ts` → `tests/unit/v194_onboarding_skip_id_and_preferred_cap.test.ts` (file rename via `git mv` to preserve history; content unchanged from the v1.93.0 push since the underlying behavior is the same).
- `preseasonRecruitingToggles.test.ts` regex updated for the broadened `(recruiting || forceRecruitingBanner) && ...` mount gate.
- Stash-pop verified: moving the new join route directory out triggers a load-error on the test file (since `read('src/app/id/[slug]/join/page.tsx')` ENOENTs), confirming the regression target is load-bearing.

Total new + carried-forward: 41 (preferred/secondary) + 19 (private join link) = **60 v1.94.0 regression tests**. Full suite: 3465 tests, 2 skipped, 0 failed.
